@startuml
title Viaverse Matching — Sequence Diagram

queue "Kafka / MSK" as Kafka
participant "matching-consumer\n(search-service)" as Matcher
participant "marketplace-service" as Marketplace
database "OpenSearch" as OpenSearch
participant "identity-service" as Identity
participant "trust-gamification" as Trust
database "Valkey / Redis" as Redis
participant "notification-service" as Notification

Kafka -> Matcher : MatchingRequested
Matcher -> Marketplace : load request snapshot
Marketplace --> Matcher : category/budget/area/urgency
Matcher -> OpenSearch : geo/category candidates
OpenSearch --> Matcher : candidate provider/business ids
Matcher -> Identity : capability/status batch check
Identity --> Matcher : eligible accounts/businesses
Matcher -> Trust : trust/risk summaries
Trust --> Matcher : score components / risk
Matcher -> Redis : availability / hot state
Redis --> Matcher : availability map
Matcher -> Matcher : score + explain reasons
Matcher -> Marketplace : persist WorkerOpportunity
Matcher -> Notification : NotificationCreated
Matcher -> Kafka : MatchingCompleted

note bottom
Matching consumes events and builds opportunities.
It does not mutate ServiceRequest source-of-truth except through explicit marketplace API/port.
end note
@enduml
